<h1>{{title}}</h1>
<div class="form-elems source-select">
  <div class="form-elem inline">
    <span class="label-container">
      <label for="source">Source</label>
    </span>
    <select id="source">
      <option value="none" data-source="none" disabled>Select a Source</option>
      <option value="inertial" data-source="inertial" selected>Inertial</option>
    </select>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="description">
  <i class="fas fa-info"></i>
  <p>You can upload any dataset you want as far as it's either a <strong>JSON</strong> or a <strong>CSV</strong> file.
    If the file is <strong>JSON</strong>, it will be automatically converted to <strong>CSV</strong> since only this
    format is considered by the system.
    Your dataset will be validated during the upload process. Hence, it can contains as much columns as needed
    but it is important for the last one to be named <strong><code>label</code></strong>.</p>
</div>
<div class="switch-group switch-large">
  <input type="radio" id="switch-raw" name="files" value="raw" checked />
  <label for="switch-raw">
    <i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i>
    Raw
  </label>
  <input type="radio" id="switch-features" name="files" value="features" />
  <label for="switch-features">
    <i class="fas fa-square-root-alt"></i>
    Features
  </label>
</div>
<div class="upload-wrapper">
  <div class="file-upload-container">
    <form method="POST" enctype="multipart/form-data">
      <input type="file" id="file-input" name="file-input">
      <label id="file-upload-label" for="file-input">
        <div class="infos">
          <i class="fas fa-upload"></i>
          <p>Drag and drop or click to upload a file</p>
          <p></p>
        </div>
        <button type="submit">Upload</button>
        <div class="progress-container">
          <p id="value"></p>
          <progress class="progress" max="100"></progress>
          <p id="cancel">
            <a href="#">Cancel</a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </label>
    </form>
  </div>
</div>
